member.name: T:Emby.Media.Model.Enums.HevcLevels
member.summary: H.265 levels according to T-REC-H.265 Annex A.
member.remarks: Attention: ffprobe returns the integer values according to the H.265 spec: The decimal level multiplied by 30. That means: 153 = 5.1 and 60 = 2.0 (not 6.0!). Opposed to that, libx265 takes values as decimal or multiplied by 10, e.g. 6.0 = 60 (6 is not allowed) To avoid disambiguity, we use decimal values at the 'output side' (Value attributes) and at the parsing side, we use decimals (allowing round-trip) and integer values (times 30), because that's we have in the database (from ffprobe).
